<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-08-1019 </DOCNO><TEXT>A systematic procedure for designing an expansion of the steam Rankinecycle to a combined cycle is proposed. The approach from the point ofview of overall thermodynamic efficiency is discussed. Practical limitationsin design considerations are also addressed. The application of thisapproach is illustrated with a typical utility system design.</TEXT></DOC>